#Text=Find a Dog by AKC Registration Number
#Text=The American Kennel Club ( AKC ) keeps a lot of information on dogs registered with the organization .
#Text=From a dog ’s competition wins and losses to its pedigree , the AKC can help you learn a lot about your furry friend .

#Text=If you know your dog ’s AKC registration number , you can use the Club ’s website to search for information about your dog , and even getting full reports on its pedigree and dog show participation .
#Text=All you need to do is register online for a free AKC account , and use the tools they provide .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Running a Free Search
#Text=Register with www.akc.org .
#Text=To research a dog on the AKC site , you will need to register for a free account with them .
#Text=Click the Sign Up link on the homepage in the upper right corner , and input your email address , your first and last name , and a password for your account .
#Text=You may need to verify your email from a link provided by the AKC website .
#Text=The AKC website is the only accurate , up-to-date source for looking up AKC registration numbers .
#Text=You can also search as a guest , but registering for an account is a good idea .
#Text=Hover over the AKC Shop in the menu bar .
#Text=Once you have registered , navigate to the ‘ shop ’ tab on the top-of-page menu bar .
#Text=Hover over the link to produce a drop-down menu .
#Text=Select the Competitor Reports option .
#Text=Competitor Reports will take you to a table of reports and searches that let you look for your dog .
#Text=Click on this link , and look under the Search Tools section .
#Text=This will be under AKC Services & Reports when accessed from the mail page .
#Text=Click on Free Dog Lookup .
#Text=Clicking directly on this link will generate a pop-up where you can search for a dog by its AKC number .
#Text=Enter the number , and click search to run your query .
#Text=Select your dog to see its information .
#Text=This search generates a limited amount of information about your dog including their birth date , sex , breed , group , breeders , owners , and some awards .
#Text=More comprehensive information may still require buying a report .
#Text=You can also search from the dog 's breed and registered name .
#Text=Finding a Dog ’s Pedigree
#Text=Register for an AKC account .
#Text=Before you can pull up any AKC reports , you need to register for an account on the AKC website .
#Text=Accounts are free , but registration will require some contact information including your name and email address .
#Text=Navigate to the AKC Shop in the menu bar .
#Text=Once you have registered with the AKC site , navigate to the ‘ Shop ’ tab on the top-of-page menu bar .
#Text=Hover over the link to produce a drop-down menu .
#Text=Select the AKC Certified Pedigrees option .
#Text=Under the ‘ Shop ’ drop-down menu , click on the ‘ AKC Certified Pedigrees ’ option .
#Text=This link will take you to a page where you can look up your dog ’s pedigree by their AKC number .
#Text=This report will show your pet 's family tree including championships , health certifications , and countries of origin for up to 4 generations .
#Text=Add the report to your cart .
#Text=To generate the search , you need to add the report to your cart .
#Text=A certified pedigree report from the AKC cost $ 34 .
#Text=You can choose to purchase a framed version of the report for an additional cost .
#Text=Input your dog ’s registration number in the search .
#Text=Once the report is in your cart , it will produce a pop-up that will allow you to search for your dog by its AKC number .
#Text=Run the search to select your dog and order the proper report .
#Text=Purchase your report .
#Text=Select the ‘ check out ’ option on the report page .
#Text=Input your credit card information and complete your purchase .
#Text=Your certified pedigree will be printed and mailed to you within a few weeks .
#Text=Tracking Your Dog ’s Awards
#Text=Register your AKC online account .
#Text=Before you can access your dog 's award records , you will need to register for an AKC online account .
#Text=Use your name and email address to sign up , and login to you account to get access to the report .
#Text=Go to the AKC Shop in the menu bar .
#Text=Just like looking up your dog ’s pedigree , you need to register for an AKC account before looking up your dog ’s awards .
#Text=Once you have registered , navigate to the ‘ shop ’ tab on the top-of-page menu bar .
#Text=Hover over the link to produce a drop-down menu .
#Text=Click on the Competitor Reports option .
#Text=This will be under the AKC Reports option .
#Text=Competitor Reports will take you to a table of reports .
#Text=Select this link , and look under the Custom Reports & Products for Your Dog section on the table .
#Text=Choose the Individual Dog Award Record and Points Progression .
#Text=This will take you to the report page , where you will be able to search your dog .
#Text=The report is an online deliverable , and costs $ 8 .
#Text=Click the button to add the report to your cart .
#Text=This will generate a pop-up where you can search for your dog by their AKC number .
#Text=Input your dog ’s number to generate their individual report .
#Text=Purchase the report .
#Text=Once you have confirmed your dog ’s registration number , you will need to purchase the report .
#Text=Select the ‘ check out ’ option on the report page and input your payment information .
#Text=The report will be delivered to you electronically .
#Text=This report will show any awards and points progressions from any AKC partner dog show or agility event .
#Text=Tips
#Text=If you do n’t know your dog ’s full AKC registration number , you can also run any of these searches using their breed and registered AKC competitor ’s name .
